%% Sequence diagram: Signup, Login and Payment flow
%% Mermaid sequenceDiagram

sequenceDiagram
  participant User as Browser/User
  participant Composer as Composer (BFF)
  participant KC_C as Keycloak (Composer realm)
  participant PaymentUI as Payment Frontend
  participant KC_P as Keycloak (Payments realm)
  participant PaymentSvc as Payment Service
  participant ComposerDB as Composer DB
  participant Notifications as Notifications Service

  Note over User,KC_C: SIGNUP / LOGIN (OIDC redirect flow)
  User->>Composer: Click "Sign up" / "Login"
  Composer-->>User: 302 Redirect to Keycloak (KC_C)
  User->>KC_C: Sign up / Login (credentials or social)
  KC_C-->>User: Redirect with Auth code -> callback to Composer
  User->>Composer: Callback (code)
  Composer->>KC_C: Exchange code for tokens (token endpoint)
  KC_C-->>Composer: ID token + access token
  Composer->>ComposerDB: Create wallet/profile (if new)
  Composer-->>User: Session established (cookie or token)

  Note over User,PaymentUI: PAYMENT FLOW (separate Payment UI + Keycloak_P)
  User->>PaymentUI: Open payment page
  PaymentUI-->>User: 302 Redirect to Keycloak (KC_P) for login if needed
  User->>KC_P: Login for Payment realm
  KC_P-->>PaymentUI: Auth code -> PaymentUI callback
  PaymentUI->>KC_P: Exchange code -> tokens
  PaymentUI->>PaymentSvc: Create Payment (auth: payment-user token)
  PaymentSvc->>Composer: POST /v1/composer/transactions (auth: composer-service-token from env)
  Composer->>ComposerDB: Persist transaction in ledger
  Composer->>Notifications: Notify user (auth via token from Composer .env)
  Notifications->>User: Send SSE / push
  PaymentSvc-->>PaymentUI: Payment result
  PaymentUI-->>User: Show success/failure
